beer_description: A medium-bodied ale balanced with rich notes of caramel and a pleasantly hoppy finish. Brewer?s favorite!

Flat Failed and Forgotten this once planned Tripel taught us NARBrewers a valuable lesson.  Beer needs the attention of a hyperactive child.  What remains is a very unique beer.  Imagine if when Indiana Jones finally found the Holy Grail, but when he did it was already filled with a dusty murky beer.  Well we have 5 gallons of it.  Chalky thick and sudsless this beer is worth trying if for no other reason than pure curiosity.  Find out more about this and other NARBrew beers at http://NARBrew.com
A crisp, American style wheat beer brewed with local wildflower honey. Add a lemon to balance this thirst-quenching customer favorite.

A lightly hopped wheat beer brewed with American & German malted barley & the lively addition of natural raspberry puree (not artificial extract). This staff favorite is fruit forward with soft pink tones, a subtly sweet finish, & a Gold Medal to boot!
This undefinable black brew is part black IPA, part American Stout, but 100% Diesel powered. Robust chocolate and roasted flavors, with thick pine hop flavor and aroma.
A robust and full-flavored ale with a fresh hop aroma that is complimented by a smooth maltiness.
Our smooth, clean, and refreshing blonde beer. A great cross-over style from domestics to lighter craft beers.
This bold and rich Irish style stout is our darkest beer on tap. Great for after dinner with notes of roasted barley, coffee, and subtle hints of dark chocolate.

Burnside IPA is our flagship brand on our sparkling new 15bbl system. An IPA with plenty of malt body and thoroughly hopped with 6 varieties of the herbaceous perennial. Expect to taste notes of pine & grapefruit in Jason?s first offering.
The original Amsterdam pale ale, available year round. Brewed with generous amounts of the finest East European hops for an exquisite floral citrus character and full flavour.

2009 SILVER MEDAL L.A. INTERNATIONAL COMMERCIAL BEER COMPETITION

  2012 SILVER MEDAL L.A. INTERNATIONAL COMMERCIAL BEER COMPETITION
Beautifully deep copper color and topped with a creamy dense head. 29 Palms Pale Ale has a mild spicy/floral aroma, and lingering hop flavor on the tongue.  Medium in body and malt flavor. Named in honor of the brave 29 Palms Marines present and past that keep us safe!  
A true ale lover?s beer!
This delicious pilsner beer is brewed in the tradition of the famous beers of the Caribbean Islands. Light bodied, crisp, clean and refreshing, with a great taste.

this American Pale Ale is brewed with the finest barley and hops. It has a deep red color and a thick creamy head. On the palate, a very nice balance between lightly toasty malts and a touch of caramel and honey sweetness.

This delicious ale combines the refreshing, soft palette of malted wheat with the abundant raspberry flavor of a traditional Belgium frambozen. It is enjoyable and refreshing especially during the summer.

Brewed at the Florida Beer Co, Melbourne, under license. La tropical represents a full-bodied beer with a strong, clean import taste, that provides a pleasant drinking experience. Its rich body leaves delicate patterns of "Brussels lace" (small bubbles of foam) in the glass, an indicative o the high quality and freshness of La Tropical.
A light amber lager with a hoppy flavor and bitterness balanced by a toasty maltiness.
An American Wheat beer with a crisp mellow maltiness balanced by fruity, spicy, hop flavors and aromas.

Burnside IPA is our flagship brand on our sparkling new 15bbl system. An IPA with plenty of malt body and thoroughly hopped with 6 varieties of the herbaceous perennial. Expect to taste notes of pine & grapefruit in Jason?s first offering.
A medium bodied English style Brown Ale with a distinctive nutty, toffee, caramel flavor and a smooth, mild finish.
Formerly called "Gaspar's Ale". A dark brown porter, medium to full-bodied. Chocolate, coffee, malt character balanced with a noticeable hop bitterness.Available December - March.

Ybor Gold Light is a light bodied Pilsner with a refreshing crisp finish that has just 105 calories and 4.3 grams carbohydrates per 12 oz bottle. This beer displays a slight hop bite. The light body of this beer make it a great summertime treat.

Key West Pilsner Light is a light-bodied, low calorie pilsner, delicately balanced between the sweetness of 100% malted barley and the crisp, finish of German hops. An average analysis shows that one 12 oz. bottle contains 82 calories, 4g carbohydrates, 1g protein, and 0g fat.
Key West Golden Lager is a light bodied, crisp, golden lager, brewed with two-row malt and fresh hops.Just right for drinking in the tropics.
A smooth creamy chocolate laden Porter. Willamette Hops. Malts: Premium Two Row, Crystal, Munich, Brown, Pale Chocolate, Chocolate. 5.8 ABV. 27 IBU
The Kirin Lager beer is made in Japan since 1888. The most famous beer in Japan.

2009 Vintage. Our Bourbon Barrel Aged Imperial Stout is complex and strong, with rich chocolate and roasty flavors.  The beer is brewed to have big malt flavor and hop bitterness to balance the sweetness of the high alcohol content.  After primary fermentation and conditioning, the beer is transferred to freshly-emptied bourbon barrels and aged for several months before being carbonated and bottled.
Crisp, hoppy taste. Clean finish. Not as much aftertaste as you get from most Ambers/Reds.

beer_description:
Ghost River Glacial Pale Ale has a healthy portion of caramel malts and gives this beer its
brilliant amber color. Brewed with Glacier hops, this new American-grown hop variety gives the beer a unique, complex flavor (mint and citrus) with a balanced clean finish.

First tapped in 1887, the Memphis Sands Aquifer remains our source for the best water in the world. It took over 125 years, but we found a way to make it even better: lots of hops. Earthy, spicy, and pungent Columbus hops help turn our favorite H2O into our favorite IPA.

Ghost River Wee Heavy is a Scottish style ale, brewed with a touch of smoked malt. This rich ale is just a "wee bit heavy", perfect for sipping on cold winter nights.

Great with chocolate desserts or as an after dinner drink.

OG 106

Like the name suggests, this toasty red ale is best by a body of water. After all, it?s brewed less than a mile away from the banks of the Mississippi. Not that we?re partial. This 2011 GABF Silver Medal winner was originally brewed for our hometown triple-A ball club, the Memphis Redbirds.

How do you brew a full-flavored but light-bodied dark beer? Some call it sorcery. We call it craftsmanship? and maybe a little sorcery. All we know is this beer keeps the roasted, malty goodness of a stout without the bitter bite. An unsuspecting crowd favorite, for sure. October - April.

The stout is traditionally a strong version of the porter, an older style. The stout is pitch black, with dark, roasted flavors with some chocolate thrown in. This is a rich beer which manages to maintain the characteristic oatmeal stout smoothness. The overall profile of this beer is of a rich, smooth stout, full of subtle undertones.

This beer was created to commemorate the 100th anniversary of the Canadian Navy. Brewed to style of a German Altbier, this easy drinking ale is perfect for any occasion!

Award winning Weissbier, Brewed by Michael Hancock using the Cool Beer facilities in Toronto.
Cloudy ochre colour with slight head and nice lacing. Yeasty sweet aroma. Yeasty bread flavour with traces of bubblegum and bananas, and spices.

A few times a year, we will cut Dan loose to brew whatever he chooses. Always handcrafted, this beer is brewed for the adventurous soul. This is a very limited edition and we make no promises to ever brew this style again. 

Do not waste time attempting to box this brew into some esoteric guide to styles. This is Dan's bold creation. His passion for unfiltered Weiss collides with Cascade Hops inventing our Imperial Hefe-Weizen. Dry hopping boldly rules over Wisconsin red wheat and our special strain of Bavarian yeast. At almost 20 O.P. this is the super mac daddy of Weiss beers. Decoction mashing was followed by excessive dry hopping to create a fierce onslaught of clove, cinnamon and citrus all in this living beer. Don't bother waiting to enjoy - the time is now.

One of the only American Hefeweizens made using the traditional Bavarian style of open fermentation. This difficult and labor-intensive technique adds uncommon depth and flavor complexity. A deeply flavorful hazy-golden hefeweizen, it is refreshing and perfect for a sunny day.

Untreated and bottled in its natural state of yeasty turbidity, this is a top fermented beer for the epicure. Its light honey colour makes it an immediate eyecatcher. Then there?s the opalescence and fine structure of the yeast turbidity. At the same time, the creamy, fine pored head invites you to get to know this light Weissbier from the Holy Mountain. First, distinctive fruity aromas like banana and honeydew melon come to the fore, followed by fine cloves. It is a very tangy, refreshing treat with the conviction of a full, soft body. It concludes on a finely balanced interplay of light sweet honey and a delicate acidity with undertones of bitter hoppiness that quickly subside into a harmonious aftertaste.

A hint of spring freshness - ideal with fine vegetables

A shiny-brass colored organic wheat beer, certified Naturland organic. An aroma of hops and citrus with a spicy note perfectly balances the malty character with the easiness of the hops. 
Refreshing and full-bodied at the same time. 
Wonderful with baguette and eggplant cream, marinated salmon with dill or roasted asparagus with tagliatelle.

Inspired by the labor-intensive process of brewing this beer in our original brewhouse, Sisyphus was our first seasonal release. Due to popular demand, it later moved into our year-round lineup. The complex citrus notes provided by a healthy portion of hops are balanced by the rich toffee undertones of the malt. Its bold, intense and warming quality makes it a great nightcap. Vintage dated ? drink it now and save some for later.

Every batch of CBC HefeWeizen is brewed with Massachusetts-grown organic wheat, which has been malted for us by our friends in Hadley, MA at Valley Malt. By the way, Weisse (white) and Weizen (wheat) are two interchangeable terms in regards to naming this style, and the words mit hefe (with yeast) indicate that this is an unfiltered beer.

So enjoy your summer with a cold CBC HefeWeizen, and show your support for sustainable, organic farms and small businesses in Massachusetts!

Hefeweizen is German for wheat beer with yeast. This golden ale utilizes a German yeast to give this beer its signature flavors, both a banana, fruity aroma and a crisp, spicy clove finish, and is served unfiltered to produce its cloudy appearance.

beer_description: Cuban Style Ale being brewed at Thomas Creek in Greenville, S.C.
Our unfiltered wheat ale has a pleasant citrus nose with a touch of bready malt character. Red wheat creates a full body and mouth feel.

Wick for Brains is our classic and painstakingly produced Fall Pumpkin Ale.? Instead of simply using spice, we use real pumpkin which lends a sweetness and pumpkin flavor not found in many Pumpkin Ales. Wonderful pumpkin pie spice intertwined in an Amber Ale creates a pumpkin sensation which is elegantly crafted.? Notes of Cinnamon, Nutmeg, Clove, Ginger and Allspice blend perfectly in this seasonal Ale. There are many Pumpkin Ales out there crafted by some wonderful breweries ? we feel that ours stands among them and in some cases ? stands apart.

An artful creation which began with our Hop God Belgian-Style IPA, enhanced by a 6 month maturation in French Oak Chardonnay Barrels. This version of Hop God is a
fascinating, big, bold Belgian-style Tripel hopped in very high amounts to concentrate
citrus, grapefruit and floral aromatics in the nose. The addition of Chardonnay barrel
aging adds further dimension and oak tannins to an already wonderfully complex Ale - bringing to mind tropical fruits and peach. We know of nothing that compares - enjoy!

A rich, full bodied Barley Wine with a wonderfully warming character from the malts & dark brown sugars. Held to the light, its burgundy color is fitting for a bigger beer that has
aromatics that hint of the oak, the whiskey, the somewhat sweet nature, and
molasses that makes this beer truly unique. The non-barrel-aged version of this beer took Silver in the 2009 US Open Beer Championships. Using Stranahan?s Whiskey
barrels, we aged this beer for 6 months to impart a small amount of oak tannins and the whiskey character that combine to elevate this beer beyond its original entry into this world. Excellent to enjoy now and cellerable for years.
